data.description: Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd. engages in the provision of cruise travel services. The company is headquartered in Miami, Florida and currently employs 36,500 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2013-01-18. The firm operates Norwegian Cruise Line, Oceania Cruises and Regent Seven Seas Cruises. With a combined fleet of 32 ships and over 66,500 berths, it offers itineraries to over 700 destinations worldwide. Its brands offer itineraries to worldwide destinations, including Europe, Asia, Australia, New Zealand, South America, Africa, Canada, Bermuda, Caribbean, Alaska and Hawaii. All its brands offer an assortment of features, amenities and activities, including a variety of accommodations, multiple dining venues, bars and lounges, spa, casino and retail shopping areas and numerous entertainment choices. All brands also offer a selection of shore excursions at each port of call, as well as air transportation and hotel packages for stays before or after a voyage. Norwegian’s ships cater to a variety of travelers with up to 20 dining options. Oceania Cruises offers onboard dining, with multiple open-seating dining venues.
